title: How DNA Is Copied
pid: ee507cf3-a967-40b2-9c53-18ca7c484655
body: |2-
  Separate the two strands.
  DNA polymerase builds the strand complementary to a single strand,
  starting at one ends and working its way along.
  That happens to both strands, and now there are two copies.
misc:
